author: CBC News
title: 44-year-old Quebec doctor dies of COVID-19
description: A 44-year-old doctor from Quebec's Montérégie region has died of COVID-19.
content:
A 44-year-old doctor from Quebec's Montérégie region has died of complications of COVID-19.
Dr. Horacio Arruda, Quebec's public health director, confirmed the doctor's death at the province's daily briefing on the pandemic Thursday.
